GEMSCAN expects config.yaml and samples.txt in the config directory.
Please use config_template.yaml as a template to create your own config.yaml file.

The samples.txt file expected a tab delimited file with these 6 columns:
sampleID	bam	index	HCgvcf	DVgvcf	STgvcf
where sampleID will the be sampleID used in the out VCF file, bam will be the full path to your bam/cram file, and index will be the full path to your bam/cram file index. Please note that even if your alignment file is in cram format, please keep the header as bam.
The last 3 columns are added for reusing the gvcf file already generated for time/resource saving in case of big build. If old reusable gvcf file existed for a particular caller, use the root path for the caller generated by GEMSCAN. E.x: /DCEG/Projects/Exome/builds/build_2024_Osteosarcoma_20240815_CGRSA-1313/GEMSCAN/deepVariant. If no reusable gvcf file, put "NO" in the corresponding column for each sample.
